                                                          <span
style="font-family:Helvetica;font-size:12px;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;font-weight:normal;letter-spacing:normal;text-align:start;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;display:inline!important">Why



                                                          does openmpi
                                                          use cores
                                                          (1,17) twice
                                                          instead of
                                                          using core
                                                          (13,29)?
